adjectives.description: tewed (comparative more tewed, superlative most tewed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, dialect) fatigued; worn from labour or hardship
examples: Sair tewed wi’ wark, I laid me down,And sloomed aneth the Roden Tree;I had a dream I’ll ne’er forgetTill Mercy’s right hand reaches me.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of tew
